  { q: "Is Stanley Cheng's Viking background relevant to Hestan service?", a: "Operationally yes, in specific ways. Stanley Cheng was president of Viking before founding Hestan in 2014, and Hestan's engineering approach reflects lessons Cheng brought from the Viking experience — heavy-duty construction philosophy, pro-grade aesthetic in a residential form factor, and a focus on serviceability. The Hestan control platform and convection architecture are newer engineering designs rather than Viking derivatives (Hestan is an independent company, not related to Middleby's Viking through corporate structure), but the overall design philosophy overlaps in meaningful ways. For service, technicians familiar with Viking wall oven diagnostic patterns transfer knowledge to Hestan with some adjustments for Hestan-specific electronics and sensor harnesses." },
  { q: "What does Hestan wall oven repair cost in LA?", a: "Residential diagnostic is $89, waived when you authorize the repair. Hestan wall oven service runs at luxury-tier pricing, with the Anaheim parts-chain advantage reducing lead times versus out-of-state luxury brands: bake element $380-$620; convection fan motor $420-$680; control board (current generation) $540-$880; temperature sensor $280-$440; door hinge $320-$520; door glass $440-$740; thermostat $340-$540; Hestan Cue firmware reset + connectivity fix $180-$320; double wall oven per-cavity service $420-$780; self-clean door-lock motor $280-$460. Anaheim distribution typical 1-2 days on common Hestan parts — genuine LA-local advantage. Specialty components (current-generation control boards, Cue-specific hardware) 3-5 days." }
