    <h2>Hestan — Anaheim California, founded 2014 by Stanley Cheng</h2>
    <p>Hestan Commercial Corporation is a relatively young luxury appliance company founded in 2014 in Anaheim, California by Stanley Cheng (who previously served as president of Viking Range Corporation). Hestan entered the market with a specific positioning angle: pro-grade engineering with California-local manufacturing, Hestan Cue smart-cook integration as a technology differentiator, and a price point positioned against the established pro-brand flagships rather than undercutting at the low end of luxury.</p>
    <p>The Anaheim headquarters is the brand's operational signature for LA service. Parts distribution runs through Anaheim directly to LA metro area, which translates to 1-2 day lead times on common Hestan service components versus 3-7 days typical for out-of-state-sourced luxury brands. For customers with Hestan wall ovens in LA + OC premium kitchens, the Anaheim proximity is a genuine service-economics advantage — we dispatch with parts faster, and specialty components that would carry long lead times from Wisconsin or Mississippi run 3-5 days from Anaheim instead.</p>
    <p>Hestan positions against Viking, Wolf, and Thermador at the luxury tier — same buyer consideration set, distinctive California-local angle plus Cue smart integration as the technology differentiator. Some LA customers prefer the Anaheim independent-manufacturer story; others prefer the established heritage of the older conglomerate-owned luxury brands. Both positions have legitimate advantages.</p>
